Requirements:
^^^^^^^^^^^^^
* SANE
* netpbm
* Apache web-server with PHP-support
* gocr (optional)

Installation:
^^^^^^^^^^^^^
Just copy the phpSANE-directory into your www-root.
Make sure that the directory "phpSANE/tmp" is writable by your
apache-user.
Then you can scan by opening phpsane.php in your web-browser.

FAQ:
^^^^
Q: My scanner isn't found by phpSANE.
A: Make sure that your apache user is able to scan with scanimage.
   Your apache user must have write-access to your scanner device, too.
   Another way to solve this problem is installing scanimage +suid-root.
